  "sections": {
    "Description": "The Firefly shoots projectiles in a direct line, similar to theTaurus Cannonweapon without push.",
    "Strategy": "The Firefly is one of the more dangerous early-game enemies. Neutralizing Fireflies, Scorpions, and Leapers should be the top priority unless there is Alpha Vek on the board.\nVery few starting Mechs are capable of single-handedly erasing 3 health in a single turn, so you should push/pull them into environmental hazards whenever possible. Moving the Firefly (or moving the Firefly's target) should be done carefully to avoid exposing additional targets to danger, since the Firefly's attack travels in a straight line across the entire board.\nThe main weakness of Fireflies is their low movement, so cutting off their positioning options is an effective way to limit what they can attack. If they go early in the Attack Order, moving another enemy into their line of fire is an effective way to neutralize them and the other threat."
  },
  "full_text": "Firefly\nDetails\nHealth\n3\nMove\n2\nSystems\nExpand\nAccelerating Thorax\n(\nEnemy\n)\nEffect\nLaunch a volatile mass of goo dealing 1 damage.\nFirefly\nis one of the\nVek\nfrom\nInto The Breach\n.\nDescription\n[\n]\nThe Firefly shoots projectiles in a direct line, similar to the\nTaurus Cannon\nweapon without push.\nStrategy\n[\n]\nThe Firefly is one of the more dangerous early-game enemies. Neutralizing Fireflies, Scorpions, and Leapers should be the top priority unless there is Alpha Vek on the board.\nVery few starting Mechs are capable of single-handedly erasing 3 health in a single turn, so you should push/pull them into environmental hazards whenever possible. Moving the Firefly (or moving the Firefly's target) should be done carefully to avoid exposing additional targets to danger, since the Firefly's attack travels in a straight line across the entire board.\nThe main weakness of Fireflies is their low movement, so cutting off their positioning options is an effective way to limit what they can attack. If they go early in the Attack Order, moving another enemy into their line of fire is an effective way to neutralize them and the other threat.\nshow\nv\n·\nd\n·\ne\nVek\nVek\nBeetle\n•\nBlobber\n•\nBurrower\n•\nCentipede\n•\nCrab\n•\nDigger\n•\nFirefly\n•\nHornet\n•\nLeaper\n•\nScarab\n•\nScorpion\n•\nSpider\n•\nVolatile Vek\nVek (Advanced Edition)\nBouncer\n•\nGastropod\n•\nMosquito\n•\nMoth\n•\nPlasmodia\n•\nStarfish\n•\nTumblebug\nAlpha Vek\nAlpha Beetle\n•\nAlpha Blobber\n•\nAlpha Burrower\n•\nAlpha Centipede\n•\nAlpha Crab\n•\nAlpha Digger\n•\nAlpha Firefly\n•\nAlpha Hornet\n•\nAlpha Leaper\n•\nAlpha Scarab\n•\nAlpha Scorpion\n•\nAlpha Spider\nAlpha Vek (Advanced Edition)\nAlpha Bouncer\n•\nAlpha Gastropod\n•\nAlpha Mosquito\n•\nAlpha Moth\n•\nAlpha Plasmodia\n•\nAlpha Starfish\n•\nAlpha Tumblebug\nVek Psions\nBlast Psion\n•\nBlood Psion\n•\nShell Psion\n•\nSoldier Psion\nVek Psions (Advanced Edition)\nArachnid Psion\n•\nRaging Psion\